@Node "Future" "PhotoCD.guide/Future"
@Next "History"
@Prev "Author"
@Toc "Main"

Future
-------

* Auto-selecting language if OS 3.1+.

* A 'save memory' option,  which means that before the conversion program
  is started, the program terminates ADPro to save memory. This is useful
  when the work directory is in Ram.

* Support for more conversion programs, just let me know if you have one,
  and then also include the possible arguments for that program.
  ("PhotoCDAGA" and "Apcd" are coming.)
@EndNode

@Node "History" "PhotoCD.guide/History"
@Next "Index"
@Prev "Future"
@Toc "Main"

History
-------

Version:       Changes:
~~~~~~~~       ~~~~~~~~

1.X.X        - Some private versions.


2.0.0        - First public release.
(6 June 94)

2.0.5        - Added a cancel button in the resolution-requester.
(14 June 94) - Added the work directory selection. Now you don't need so
               much memory anymore.
             - Improved  preferences,  with  the  standard choices  when
               saving the preferences.
             - Improved directory-check control.
             - Improved guide.

2.1          - Added support for the @{"hpcdtoppm" Link Requirements} program.
(3 January   - Added auto-recognition of conversion-program.
 1995)       - Changed @{"version" Link Main} number layout.
             - Changed the default work directory from "Ram:T" to "T:".
             - Added some requestors for version messages.
             - Changed  the  default  conversion  program  directory  to
               "DH0:Graphics".
@Endnode

